---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Boundary from "../components/Boundary.astro";
---

<Base>
  <!-- Hero: calm, serious, hopeful. Mission in two sentences. -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow rise rise-1">The Human-Core Initiative</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title rise rise-2">
        A free, open, evidence-based framework for human development in the age
        of AI.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-lede rise rise-3">
        We build on what the science of learning already shows, and we point AI
        at empowering teachers and teaching children to master it, never at
        surveilling them. Open to everyone, owned by no company.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions rise rise-4">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/resources">Explore the free resources</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/principles">Read the principles</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The two-crisis problem, in brief. -->
  <section class="wrap problem">
    <p class="eyebrow">The problem, in brief</p>
    <h2>Two crises, and they compound.</h2>
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-item">
        <p class="section-no">01</p>
        <h3>Children are not learning the foundations</h3>
        <p>
          The World Bank estimates that around seven in ten 10-year-olds in low-
          and middle-income countries cannot read and understand a simple story,
          a figure that rose from 57% to roughly 70% through the pandemic.
          Wealthy systems are not exempt: foundational skills in reading and
          mathematics are declining across many developed countries too. Too
          often, teaching is unresponsive, and teachers are given almost no
          usable feedback on their own practice.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-item">
        <p class="section-no">02</p>
        <h3>AI changes what learning is for, and how it is avoided</h3>
        <p>
          AI now does most of what the old system trained children for, while
          also giving them a frictionless way to avoid the thinking that builds
          their minds. A system that was already failing to develop children is
          now also obsolete in its aims and newly easy to cheat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="problem-close">
      This initiative exists to act on both crises at once, in the open,
      globally, rather than to complain about them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The boundary: the signature. -->
  <section class="wrap boundary-section">
    <Boundary />
  </section>

  <!-- The three pillars, in one line each. -->
  <section class="wrap pillars-teaser">
    <p class="eyebrow">The three pillars</p>
    <h2>One synthesis, three pieces.</h2>
    <ol class="pillar-list">
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>An open, evidence-based pedagogy</h3>
          <p>
            A complete, age-banded curriculum and methods guide any teacher or
            parent can adopt without permission or payment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>AI that empowers teachers</h3>
          <p>
            A private, teacher-owned coach that listens to the teaching, not to
            the children's feelings, and turns coaching from a luxury into
            something every teacher can have.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>AI mastery for children</h3>
          <p>
            Teaching children to use AI as a thinking partner they control, to
            audit it for error and bias, and to stay in charge of their own
            minds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <a class="text-link" href="/pillars">Read each pillar in plain language <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
  </section>

  <!-- Closing CTA -->
  <section class="wrap closing-section">
    <div class="closing">
      <h2>Start with the teacher workbook.</h2>
      <p>
        The Pillar 3 Teacher Workbook is the most complete draw: eight
        ready-to-run sessions that teach children to use, question, and
        out-think AI, with printable materials so it works even without AI in
        the room.
      </p>
      <div class="closing-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/resources/pillar-3-teacher-workbook">Open the workbook</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/about">About this work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 6.5rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6.2vw, 4.3rem);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 0;
  }
  .hero-lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.2vw, 1.45rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2.2rem; }

  section { scroll-margin-top: 6rem; }
  .problem { padding-top: 3.5rem; }
  .problem > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) { .problem-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; } }
  .problem-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.7rem;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .problem-item p { color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .problem-close {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.6vw, 1.7rem);
    line-height: 1.4;
    max-width: 36rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .boundary-section { margin-top: 4.5rem; }

  .pillars-teaser { margin-top: 4.5rem; }
  .pillars-teaser > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .pillar-list { list-style: none; margin: 2rem 0 0; padding: 0; display: grid; gap: 0; }
  .pillar-list li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.6rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
  }
  .pillar-list li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line); }
  .pillar-n {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--color-clay);
    line-height: 1;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 40;
  }
  .pillar-list h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
  .pillar-list p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-ink-soft); max-width: 48rem; }
  .text-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .closing-section { margin-top: 4.5rem; }
  .closing {
    background: var(--color-pine-tint);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-pine) 18%, var(--color-line));
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
  }
  .closing h2 { font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3.6vw, 2.4rem); margin: 0; }
  .closing p { color: var(--color-ink-soft); max-width: 44rem; margin: 1rem 0 0; font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .closing-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.8rem; }
</style>
